Why this patch:
  Kibana flattens axios's `exports['.'].types` to a single `index.d.ts`. With
  module:commonjs + moduleResolution:bundler, TS would otherwise pick the
  "require" condition and resolve to `index.d.cts` (a structurally different,
  namespace-shaped declaration). That triggers TS2883 in declaration emit
  ("cannot be named without a reference to ../axios/index.cjs") for inferred
  AxiosResponse return types in generated clients.
  We avoid the alternative `tsconfig.base.json#paths.axios -> index.d.ts`
  workaround because tsconfig `paths` are also consumed by runtime tools
  (tsx via Cypress, rspack), which then try to execute the .d.ts as JS.
  See PR #170856 / issue #171080.

diff --git a/node_modules/axios/package.json b/node_modules/axios/package.json
--- a/node_modules/axios/package.json
+++ b/node_modules/axios/package.json
@@ -11,10 +11,7 @@
   "typings": "./index.d.ts",
   "exports": {
     ".": {
-      "types": {
-        "require": "./index.d.cts",
-        "default": "./index.d.ts"
-      },
+      "types": "./index.d.ts",
       "bun": {
         "require": "./dist/node/axios.cjs",
         "default": "./index.js"
